  "title": "Exploring Rhythm Patterns",
  "lessonText": "Understanding rhythm is essential for playing piano effectively.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- Rhythm is the pattern of sounds and silences in music.\n- It is created by combining different note values.\n- Common note values include whole notes, half notes, quarter notes, and eighth notes.\n- Time signatures indicate how many beats are in each measure.\n- Practice clapping or tapping out various rhythm patterns to internalize them."
  }
}
